# Services & Repositories

## Every Service Must Answer

```
Why does this service exist?
```

If you cannot state its purpose in one sentence, split it.

## Responsibilities

| Layer | Owns |
|-------|------|
| **Services** | Workflows, orchestration, business rules, transaction boundaries |
| **Repositories** | Data access only — queries, inserts, updates, deletes |

## Rules

- Services orchestrate one or more repositories.
- Repositories **never** call another repository.
- Services **can** call multiple repositories.
- Business rules live in services (or domain layer), not in repositories.
- Transaction boundaries are opened in services, not repositories.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — repository calls another repository
class BookingRepository {
  async create(data) {
    const asset = await assetRepository.findById(data.assetId); // violation
    return prisma.booking.create({ data });
  }
}

// ✅ GOOD — service orchestrates
class BookingService {
  async create(userId, data) {
    const asset = await this.assetRepo.findById(data.assetId);
    if (!asset) throw new NotFoundError('Asset');
    return this.bookingRepo.create({ ...data, createdBy: userId });
  }
}
```
